# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- In this code we first sort the stones to get the 2 heaviest stones at the end of the array.
- Now we repetedly smashes(calculates the diff of the two heaviest stones,then setting the heaviest stone with that diff and second heaviest stone with 0) the two heaviest stones until there is only one stone left.
- Again sort the stones after the smash.
- This loop ends when the weigth of the second heaviest stone is 0.
- This indicates that there is only one stone left.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n^2 log n)
