# Explanation
- At any point of time we need largest 2 stones that's why I used priority queue.
- If the diffrence of these two stones is > 0, the we push it in the queue.
- And if diffrence is 0, i.e. both stones are destroyed
- At the end of the loop is the queue is empty, i.e. all the stones were destroyed during the game, that means we have to return 0
- Else we just return the last stone that's left in the queue.

