solutions.content:
The Idea :
If we can swap the rows such that we can get a `Binary Grid`

1. For i'th row to be fulfilled, there should be a row with (n - i - 1) trailing zeros 
2. If we can't find a candidate row then we can't get a 'Binary Grid'
3. If we found a candidate row, then we need to bubble it to the i'th index, since we can ONLY SWAP ADJECENT ROWS, we need |candidateIndex - i| swaps. And need to actually swap the items so that the subsequent steps can operate on the resulted array


```
public int minSwaps(int[][] grid) {
        int[] numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow = new int[grid.length];

        // below is to fill up the numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow array
        for (int i = 0; i < grid.length; ++i) {
            for (int j = grid.length - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
                if (grid[i][j] == 0) {
                    numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow[i]++;
                } else {
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        int n = numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow.length;
        int count = 0;

        // we need to change the numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow such that
        // each index `i` has at least (n - i - 1) trailing zeros

        // iterate through the numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            // the candidate row should have at least `requiredZerosAtThisIndex` trailing zeros
            int requiredZerosAtThisIndex = n - i - 1;

            //  let's find a candidate row to be the i'th row, no need to start from beginning, we should have fixed each previous rows, so no need to consider prevous ones 
            for (int j = i; j < n; ++j) {
                // this is the condition to be a candidate for i'th row
                if (numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow[j] >= requiredZerosAtThisIndex) {
                    // since we found the candidate row, bubble-up the candidate row to the i'th position
                    for (int k = j; k > i; --k) {
                        int temp = numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow[k];
                        numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow[k] = numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow[k - 1];
                        numberOfTrailingZerosAtEachRow[k - 1] = temp;

						// let's count how many steps it took to bubble up, ultimately this is the answer we want right !!!
                        count++;
                    }

                    // we filled the i'th position, let's continue with the next position
                    break;
                }

                // if this is true, okay we have reached the end of the array, and we didn't find a candidate for the i'th row
                if (j == n - 1) {
                    return -1;
                }
            }
        }

        // return the swap count
        return count;
    }

