solutions.content:
**APPROACH**
We want zeros on upper triange of the matrix so for every row we need to find if there exist a row in required format.Like 
say **n=4** the required formats are
Row 1  **x000**
Row 2  **xx00**
Row 3  **xxx0**
Row 4  **xxxx**

**Here if our answer exist it will be in above format with rows distorted like instead of R1234 it can be R3214 or R1423 so we need to just find the required row position.** Now say at ith row we start seeking the row which fits with ith format and we get that at xth position then we can reach there by swapping every row above x consequently till we reach i that is (x-i) swaps. 
We'll do it for every row and count number of swaps. 
Since there can be multiple rows fitting in a format (like for xxx0 it can be 1010 or 1000) we'll take the one which is nearer because we need to minimize the swaps.
..
**Wait.... how will you check the format??
Its simple use prefix sum from right.
Like for R = xx00 if a row satisfies the format then at index 1 sum will be either (0 or 1 if R[1]==1)**

**Walk through the Code**

```
class Solution {
public:
    int minSwaps(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        vector<vector<int>> v=grid;
        int n=grid.size();
        if(n==1) return grid[0][0]==1?0:-1;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=n-2;j>=0;j--){
                v[i][j]+=v[i][j+1];                  // Building prefix sum array from right  end
            }
        }

        int c=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){
            if(v[i][i]>1 || (grid[i][i]==0 && v[i][i]==1)){             //If row doesn't satisfies the format
                int idx=-1;                                               
                for(int x=i+1;x<n;x++){                                      // Start searching from below
                    if(v[x][i]==0 || (v[x][i]==1 && grid[x][i]==1)){
                        idx=x;                                                         //Stop immediately as you get the format
                        break;
                    }
                }
                if(idx==-1) return -1;                                    //If we can't find the format return -1
                c+=(idx-i);

                v.insert(v.begin()+i,v[idx]);                            //Insert the (idx)th to ith position and remove it from prev position 
                grid.insert(grid.begin()+i,grid[idx]);
                v.erase(v.begin()+idx+1);                               //Do the same insertion and deletion to both original and prefix arrays
                grid.erase(grid.begin()+idx+1);

            }
        }
        return c;

    }
};
```
